                        debug debugging loop reproduce failure read first error change one thing rerun smallest test                                                                    Debugging loop                                                  Reproduce the failure, read the first error, change one thing, and rerun the smallest test.                                                                                                     test strategy name behavior choose smallest proof run record pass fail                                                                                          Test strategy                                                   Name the behavior, choose the smallest proof, run it, and record pass or fail.                                                                                                                  review code look first correctness regressions missing tests unclear ownership risky edge cases                                                                 Code review                                                     Look first for correctness, regressions, missing tests, unclear ownership, and risky edge cases.                                                                                                release check verify tests logs artifact names checksums notes target tag                                                                                       Release check                                                   Verify tests, logs, artifact names, checksums, release notes, and the target tag.                                                                                                               rollback plan know previous good version command restore evidence worked                                                                                        Rollback plan                                                   Know the previous good version, the command to restore it, and the evidence that rollback worked.                                                                                               perf performance check measure before changing code isolate hot path compare same workload after change                                                         Performance check                                               Measure before changing code, isolate the hot path, and compare the same workload after the change.                                                                                             architecture note state goal constraints data flow failure modes next reversible step                                                                           Architecture note                                               State the goal, constraints, data flow, failure modes, and the next reversible step.                                                                                                            triage issue classify impact reproduction quality affected surface owner next action                                                                            Issue triage                                                    Classify impact, reproduction quality, affected surface, owner, and next action.                                                                                                                modern 486 llm path small hot-loaded weights compact retrieval databases persistent memory short synthesis replies                                              Modern 486 LLM path                                             Use small hot-loaded weights, compact retrieval databases, persistent memory, and short synthesis replies.                                                                                      language pack design carry model path persona actions kdb.txt user.txt evidence gates                                                                           Language pack design                                            A language pack should carry model path, persona, actions, KDB.TXT, USER.TXT, and evidence gates.                                                                                               hot load weights hot-loaded switch packs only domain changes reuse already loaded model paths match                                                             Hot-loaded weights                                              Switch packs only when the domain changes, and reuse the already loaded model when paths match.                                                                                                 retrieval first answer kdb user notes memory golden rows before asking small model synthesize                                                                   Retrieval first                                                 Answer from KDB, USER notes, memory, and golden rows before asking the small model to synthesize.                                                                                               database recall high velocity compile notes compact keyword rows dos scans less text reaches answer faster                                                      High velocity recall                                            Compile notes into compact keyword rows so DOS scans less text and reaches the answer faster.                                                                                                   local override notes put site facts user.txt knowledge bundled pack database                                                                                    Local override notes                                            Put site facts in USER.TXT so local knowledge can override the bundled pack database.                                                                                                           memory persistence persistent save stable facts assist.mem keep transient previous-turn context separate                                                        Persistent memory                                               Save stable facts to ASSIST.MEM and keep transient previous-turn context separate.                                                                                                              quality gate useful checks novel phrasings exact output terms runtime logs artifact checksums                                                                   Quality gate                                                    A useful gate checks novel phrasings, exact output terms, runtime logs, and artifact checksums.                                                                                                 qemu proof repeatable dos evidence confirm timing behavior physical hardware                                                                                    QEMU proof                                                      Use QEMU for repeatable DOS evidence, then confirm timing and behavior on physical hardware.                                                                                                    hardware target 486-friendly assistant minimize disk reads memory churn context length generated tokens                                                         Hardware target                                                 A 486-friendly assistant should minimize disk reads, memory churn, context length, and generated tokens.                                                                                        pack authoring write help know rows rebuild kdb run validator retrieval qemu gates                                                                              Pack authoring                                                  Write HELP and KNOW rows, rebuild KDB, run the authoring validator, then run retrieval and QEMU gates.                                                                                          failure record command input expected result actual log path next experiment                                                                                    Failure record                                                  Record the command, input, expected result, actual result, log path, and next experiment.                                                                                                       data sharding kdb grows large split topic shards bucket files before changing model                                                                             Data sharding                                                   When KDB grows large, split it into topic shards or bucket files before changing the model.                                                                                                     answer synthesis retrieval facts model short wording transitions adapting prompt                                                                                Answer synthesis                                                Use retrieval for facts and the model for short wording, transitions, and adapting the answer to the prompt.                                                                                    trust model improves every answer path cite local files memory tests generated evidence records                                                                 Trust model                                                     Trust improves when every answer path can cite local files, memory, tests, or generated evidence records.                                                                                       